title: For Sale/Trade:  Ithaca AFPG 1911
postcontent:
This is an M1911A1. The slide is an Ithaca slide with the serial number beginning with AF. This AF stands for Air Force. The slide for this pistol is Ithaca AFPG (Air Force Premium Grade), it was made somewhere between the years of 1958 and 1970 by Air Force Armories. They are distinguished competition grade M1911A1's for use by the Air Force Shooting team, very rare and very precise. Complete AFPG pistols sell for over $3,000 in 100% condition, this however is not a matching pistol. 

The frame on this pistol is still a mystery to me, even with all the help I am receiving I am still unable to pinpoint its origins. I can tell you lower is in great condition and has a very smooth trigger pull, reminds me of my Kimber. 

The grips on this pistol are Pachmayr grips made in LA, USA. On the inside of the grips it reads, "Colt .45"

Email works but I prefer texts 1-REDACTED

Description

The Mosin-Nagant 91/30 is a bolt-action rifle chambered in 7.62X54mmR. The Mosin-Nagant 91/30 was introduced to the Russian/USSR military in 1891 and stayed in service until the end of World War II. In fact, it became the standard issue service rifle beginning in 1930 to all Russian soldiers and, during WWII, commonly used as a sniper rifle. It has standard features for a military rifle of its time such as iron sights, wooden stock and bayonet stud.
